        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:52AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1252 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Broadford, or near Saltville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Marion...
Saltville...
Chilhowie...
Nebo...
Asberrys...
Hungry Mother State Park...
and Broadford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
